  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Paella de marisco is a Spanish seafood rice dish where the flavour comes from the stock and the sofrito as much as from the shellfish. The rice cooks in a concentrated seafood stock and forms a "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "socarrat",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "socarrat"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " on the base. The seafood goes in during the last few minutes of cooking to keep it tender. Do not stir the rice once the stock is added."
          }
        ]
      },
